6]]\n! [[List of earthquakes in 2017|2017]]\n! [[List of earthquakes in 2018|2018]]\n! [[List of earthquakes in 2019|2019]]\n!style=\"background:#efefef;\"| ''2020''\n|-\n! 8.0\u20139.9\n| 1\n| 1\n| 2\n| 2\n| 1\n| 1\n| 0\n| 1\n| 1\n| 1\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|0\n|-\n! 7.0\u20137.9\n| 21\n| 19\n| 15\n| 17\n| 11\n| 18\n| 16\n| 6\n| 16\n| 9\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|3\n|-\n! 6.0\u20136.9\n| 151\n| 204\n| 129\n| 125\n| 140\n| 124\n| 128\n| 106\n| 117\n| 133\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|28\n|-\n! 5.0\u20135.9\n| 1,963\n| 2,271\n| 1,412\n| 1,402\n| 1,475\n| 1,413\n| 1,502\n| 1,451\n| 1,675\n| 1,489\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|395\n|-\n! 4.0\u20134.9\n| 10,164\n| 13,303\n| 10,990\n| 9,795\n| 13,494\n| 13,239\n| 12,771\n| 11,296\n| 12,777\n| 11,337\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|3,031\n|-\n! Total\n| 12,309\n| 15,798\n| 12,548\n| 11,341\n| 15,121\n| 14,795\n| 14,420\n| 12,860\n| 14,586\n| 12,973\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|3,458\n|}\n\nAn increase in detected earthquake numbers does not necessarily represent an increase in earthquakes ''per se''. Population increase, habitation spread, and advances in earthquake detection technology all contribute to higher earthquake numbers being recorded over time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usgs.gov/faq/taxonomy/term/9830|title=USGS Earthquake Myths|publisher=[[United States Geological Survey]]|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319120417/http://www.usgs.gov/faq/taxonomy/term/9830|archivedate=March 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==By death toll==\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%;\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Death toll\n! Magnitude\n! Location\n! [[Mercalli intensity scale|MMI]]\n! Depth (km)\n! Date\n|-\n|1\n|41\n|6.7\n|{{flagicon|Turkey}} [[2020 Elaz\u0131\u011f earthquake|Turkey]], [[Elaz\u0131\u011f Province|Elaz\u0131\u011f]]\n| {{MMI-ts|desc=1|IX}}\n|{{nts|10.0}}\n|{{dts|January 24}}\n|-\n|2\n|10\n|5.8\n|{{flag|Iran}}, [[West Azerbaijan Province|West Azerbaijan]]\n| {{MMI-ts|de