-sukabumi-tidak-ada-korban-jiwa|title=Gempa Sukabumi, Tidak Ada Korban Jiwa|last=BeritaSatu.com|website=beritasatu.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-10}}</ref>\n| -\n|2\n|-\n|14<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/eventpage/us60008fl8/executive|title=M 6.3 - 298km NE of Raoul Island, New Zealand|website=earthquake.usgs.gov|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n|{{flag|New Zealand}}, [[Kermadec Islands]] offshore, 298 km northeast of [[Raoul Island]]\n|6.3\n|10.0\n|III\n| -\n| -\n| -\n|-\n|17<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/eventpage/us60008h76/executive|title = M 6.0 - 167km E of Hihifo, Tonga|website=earthquake.usgs.gov|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n|{{flag|Tonga}}, [[Niuatoputapu]] offshore, 167 km east of [[Hihifo]]\n|6.0\n|10.0\n|IV\n| The island of [[Samoa]] was shaken, although the epicentre was in Tonga.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/world/samoa-shaken-5-8-magnitude-earthquake|title=Samoa shaken by 5.8 magnitude earthquake|work=TVNZ|access-date=2020-03-18|language=en-NZ}}</ref>\n| -\n| -\n|-\n|18<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/eventpage/us60008hkg/executive| title = M 6.1 - 100km NW of Sola, Vanuatu|website=earthquake.usgs.gov|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n|{{flag|Vanuatu}}, [[Torba Province|Torba]] offshore, 100 km northwest of [[Sola, Vanuatu|Sola]]\n|6.1\n|178.8\n|IV\n| -\n| -\n| -\n|-\n|18<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/eventpage/uu60363602/executive| title = M 5.7 - 4km NNE of Magna, Utah|website=earthquake.usgs.gov|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n|{{flag|United States}}, [[Utah]], 4 km north northeast of [[Magna, Utah|Magna]]\n|5.7\n|11.9\n|VIII\n|The '''[[2020 Salt Lake City earthquake]]''' was the strongest earthquake in [[Utah]] since 1992. More than 50,000 people lost power in [[Salt Lake City]], and some damage was reported to houses and buildings.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/earthquake-salt-lake-city-5