</ref>\n|{{flag|Greece}}, [[Epirus (region)|Epirus]], 15 km southeast of [[Paramythia]]\n|5.7\n|10.0\n|VII\n|Some old buildings were damaged and various collapsed in [[Kanalaki greece|Kanalaki]]. Three people were slightly injured.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://greece.greekreporter.com/2020/03/21/magnitude-5-6-earthquake-strikes-north-western-greece/|title=Magnitude 5.6 Earthquake Strikes North-Western Greece|website=greece.greekreporter.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.china.org.cn/world/Off_the_Wire/2020-03/21/content_75843166.htm|title=Three injured, houses damaged after quake shakes western Greece - China.org.cn|website=www.china.org.cn|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n| -\n| 3\n|-\n|22<ref>{{cite web |title=M 5.4 - 3km SW of Kasina, Croatia |url=https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/eventpage/us70008dx7/executive |website=earthquake.usgs.gov |accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n|{{flag|Croatia}}, [[City of Zagreb]], 3 km southwest of [[Ka\u0161ina]]\n|5.4\n|10.0\n|VII\n|The '''[[2020 Zagreb earthquake]]''' was the strongest earthquake to hit the city since the [[1880 Zagreb earthquake|1880 earthquake]]. Serious damage was caused, more than 26,000 buildings were damaged, and some collapsed. One teenager was critically injured by a roof and died later in the hospital, while another 26 people were wounded.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.post-gazette.com/news/world/2020/03/22/Croatia-quake-injures-17-amid-partial-coronavirus-lockdown/stories/202003220140|title=Croatia quake injures 17 amid partial coronavirus lockdown|website=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Tinejd\u017eerica stradala u potresu i dalje je kriti\u010dno. U potresu ozlije\u0111eno 27 ljudi |url=https://www.index.hr/vijesti/clanak/tinejdzerica-stradala-u-potresu-i-dalje-je-kriticno-u-potresu-ozlijedjeno-27-ljudi/2167911.aspx |website=index.hr |accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n| 26\n|-\n|22<ref>{{Cite 